result.execSummary:
The defendant Jesus QUINONES-CHAVEZ was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

The State files an Amended Information which charges 1 count misdemeanor battery-dvo, contrary to Sections 940.19(1) and 968.075(1)(a)  and 1 count disorderly conduct-dvo, contrary to Sections 947.01(1) and 968.075(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
NO CONTEST pleas entered to both counts contained in the Amended Information.  Convicted.
On count 1, battery/dvo, the defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for twenty-five (25) days, time already served.
Defendant has credit for 20 days.
On count 2, disorderly conduct/dvo, the defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for twenty-five (25) days, under the Huber Law, consecutive to count 1, commencing on 11-25-14 by 6:00 p.m.
Total court costs for both counts is $923.00.  $300.00 cash bail applied.  $623.00 balance is to be paid by 02-21-2015 or 13 days county jail for failure to pay.
